14 WHEREAS, he has additionally been involved in numerous civic and professional
15 organizations, including as a past board member of the Georgia Bible Camp Organization
16 and past director of the Valdosta Touchdown Club; and
17 WHEREAS, outside of his professional accomplishments, Franklin Bailey is a devoted
18 husband to his wife, Sabrina; a loving father to his two sons, Jarod and Travis; and a proud
19 grandfather; and
20 WHEREAS, this distinguished gentleman has given inspiration to many through his high
21 ideals, morals, and deep concern for his fellow citizens, and he possesses the vast wisdom
22 which only comes through experience and the strength of character which is achieved
23 through overcoming the many challenges of life; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
25 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately honored.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend Franklin Bailey for his many invaluable
28 contributions to both the home building industry and his community as well as extend best
29 wishes for continued success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
32 Franklin Bailey.
